1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:06,172
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:11,177
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:16,641 --> 00:00:18,309
[Peping] <i>Did someone move Saint Anthony?</i>

4
00:00:18,393 --> 00:00:20,395
Why isn't the statue in its proper place?

5
00:00:20,478 --> 00:00:22,480
[Siony] Someone took it from the church!

6
00:00:22,564 --> 00:00:23,732
Whoever did it must be an outsider!

7
00:00:23,815 --> 00:00:25,442
But no one new has come around.

8
00:00:26,025 --> 00:00:28,278
[Paldo] Father, you're mistaken.
He just came back.

9
00:00:28,361 --> 00:00:30,989
[Atoy] <i>I don't get why I'm the one</i>
<i>you're all pointing fingers at.</i>

10
00:00:31,072 --> 00:00:32,198
Where are your things?

11
00:00:32,282 --> 00:00:34,868
[Atoy] <i>Disappointed</i>
<i>you didn't find the statue?</i>

12
00:00:34,951 --> 00:00:39,247
Ever since you turned your back on me,
you've changed.

13
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:43,001
[Atoy] <i>Maybe you should take</i>
<i>a hard look at yourself,</i>

14
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:44,502
<i>because this is on you.</i>

15
00:00:44,586 --> 00:00:47,464
[Atoy] If there was
no break-in from outside,

16
00:00:47,547 --> 00:00:50,884
then the thief
must have stayed inside, right?

17
00:00:51,509 --> 00:00:55,305
Do any of you know someone who eats
Biscocho, or has been to Bacolod?

18
00:00:55,388 --> 00:00:56,264
Why me?

19
00:00:56,347 --> 00:00:58,558
Don't blame me. I've been
trying to stay out of trouble.

20
00:00:58,641 --> 00:01:02,437
[man] <i>Didn't you say your girlfriend</i>
<i>from Bacolod was coming to visit?</i>

21
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:04,856
[Delfin] My past is catching up with me.

22
00:01:04,939 --> 00:01:07,150
I think our son already knows
what I did to you.

23
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:09,486
[Cita] <i>Saint Anthony</i>
<i>can still work a miracle.</i>

24
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:10,820
[Cita] When he returns,

25
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:14,699
maybe that will be the moment for you
and your father to finally reconcile.

26
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:19,287
I'm sorry that I couldn't
do anything to help you both.

27
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:22,082
[congregation] Oh, Hail Mary,
full of grace.

28
00:01:22,165 --> 00:01:23,917
The Lord is with you.

29
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,877
Blessed are you among women.

30
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:28,171
And blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus.

31
00:01:28,254 --> 00:01:31,174
[congregation] Holy Mary,
Mother of God, pray for us sinners…

32
00:01:31,257 --> 00:01:35,011
Father, I searched Paldo's house myself,

33
00:01:35,094 --> 00:01:39,224
but the statue wasn't there,
so I confronted him.

34
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:42,727
He still refused to tell me anything.

35
00:01:43,978 --> 00:01:45,522
[congregation] Holy Mary,
Mother of God, pray for us sinners…

36
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:47,023
Father Peping!

37
00:01:47,106 --> 00:01:48,274
[whimsical music]

38
00:01:48,358 --> 00:01:49,859
Father Peping!

39
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:52,028
Father Peping!

40
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:54,030
Fa-- Father Peping!

41
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:55,990
Fa-- Father Peping,

42
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:57,659
I remember now.

43
00:01:57,742 --> 00:01:58,952
I finally remember!

44
00:01:59,035 --> 00:02:00,912
I remember now!

45
00:02:00,995 --> 00:02:05,166
[stammers] I saw Saint Anthony last night.

46
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:07,710
Mmm-hmm!

47
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:11,381
- Did you see who took him?
- Yes, I did.

48
00:02:12,298 --> 00:02:13,341
[Nestor] <i>He was floating sideways.</i>

49
00:02:14,425 --> 00:02:18,054
[Emerson] What? Floating sideways?

50
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,973
You're probably making
this up, Sir Nestor.

51
00:02:20,056 --> 00:02:21,015
[Nestor] No, no! You…

52
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:22,976
You listen to me. You listen to me!

53
00:02:23,059 --> 00:02:23,935
[man mutters]

54
00:02:24,018 --> 00:02:24,853
Father…

55
00:02:25,562 --> 00:02:27,313
I wasn't that drunk, and…

56
00:02:27,397 --> 00:02:29,899
I saw it, I really did.

57
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:34,320
- I saw it floating sideways,
- [man laughs]

58
00:02:35,029 --> 00:02:38,449
then it drifted away
from the church, Father.

59
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:41,494
[Nestor] <i>Then, it went into a passage…</i>

60
00:02:43,788 --> 00:02:47,542
And then… it disappeared.

61
00:02:47,625 --> 00:02:49,002
[crowd gasping] Huh?!

62
00:02:49,085 --> 00:02:50,086
It vanished.

63
00:02:51,754 --> 00:02:54,465
- I even heard a little sound effect…
- [woman mutters]

64
00:02:54,549 --> 00:02:55,675
[car door clicks shut]

65
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:57,635
- Shzzug.
- [crowd buzzing]

66
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:59,304
[muttering]

67
00:03:01,347 --> 00:03:02,473
[Paldo] Sir Nestor…

68
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:03,933
[Emerson] What shzzug?

69
00:03:04,017 --> 00:03:06,060
Where could Saint Anthony be?

70
00:03:07,228 --> 00:03:09,856
Maybe he ended up in Encantadia.

71
00:03:09,939 --> 00:03:12,483
[Nestor] No, no, no, no!

72
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:13,776
[suave music playing]

73
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:15,403
- It went to…
- Where?

74
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:16,863
A black hole.

75
00:03:17,655 --> 00:03:19,908
[suave music continues]

76
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:24,412
[Emerson laughing]

77
00:03:24,495 --> 00:03:26,122
Yes, it got sucked into a black hole,

78
00:03:26,205 --> 00:03:29,542
and then you heard this "shzzug" sound.
What happened after that?

79
00:03:29,626 --> 00:03:30,543
A "shzzugsh" sound afterwards.

80
00:03:30,627 --> 00:03:32,211
I had been drinking, but…

81
00:03:33,338 --> 00:03:35,506
I saw it myself. Father,
you have to believe me.

82
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:37,592
[Nestor] I really did. It's true!

83
00:03:37,675 --> 00:03:39,761
I had a drink, but I wasn't that drunk3

84
00:03:39,844 --> 00:03:42,096
- [woman] Whatever!
- It saw it!

85
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:44,307
[Nestor] It was floating sideways,
just like this!

86
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:46,559
Sir Nestor, you should go home.
You reek of alcohol!

87
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:47,936
You shouldn't be here at all.

88
00:03:48,519 --> 00:03:49,771
Go home.

89
00:03:49,854 --> 00:03:51,856
Uh, Father…

90
00:03:52,815 --> 00:03:55,401
Sir Nestor, let's go.
Let me take you home.

91
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:56,986
Come on. Let's go.

92
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:58,905
- [Nestor] I saw what I saw.
- Come on.

93
00:03:58,988 --> 00:04:00,740
- [Peping] Get some rest.
- Let's go.

94
00:04:00,823 --> 00:04:02,325
[Emerson] Come on, Father.

95
00:04:02,408 --> 00:04:06,037
[curious music continues]

96
00:04:06,621 --> 00:04:08,164
[Atoy] Sir Nestor, where were you standing

97
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:11,793
when you saw Saint Anthony floating?

98
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:13,795
Come here, Atoy.

99
00:04:16,714 --> 00:04:19,050
Here. I was standing here, then…

100
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:20,301
There, right there, right there.

101
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:22,220
That's where I saw it. Over there.

102
00:04:22,303 --> 00:04:23,346
[inquisitive music playing]

103
00:04:23,429 --> 00:04:26,891
The lights are out, so anyone at
the perimeter wouldn't have seen anything.

104
00:04:26,975 --> 00:04:28,142
Did you hear anything else?

105
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:29,727
It was completely quiet.

106
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:32,313
Anyway, I saw it floating right there.

107
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:33,898
Yes, right over there.

108
00:04:33,982 --> 00:04:35,608
- Then, I heard a…
- [car door clicks shut]

109
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:37,527
- Shzzug. Yes, that's it!
- Shzzug.

110
00:04:37,610 --> 00:04:39,445
- Something like that! That's it.
- Shzzug.

111
00:04:39,529 --> 00:04:41,656
That's what the passage sounds like…

112
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:43,950
- I heard a shzzug.
- Shzzug.

113
00:04:48,663 --> 00:04:51,040
Sir Nestor, you might be thinking of…

114
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:58,423
Could it have just been covered
by this black tarpaulin?

115
00:04:58,506 --> 00:05:00,300
That would explain why
you thought it was floating,

116
00:05:00,383 --> 00:05:02,093
because the person was dressed in black

117
00:05:02,176 --> 00:05:05,847
and lying sideways with the cloth
draped over their shoulders.

118
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:07,890
It only appeared to be floating

119
00:05:07,974 --> 00:05:10,310
because of the way
they were positioned and moving.

120
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:16,107
And maybe that passage you mentioned
was just a black car.

121
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:20,278
And the "shzzug" sound…
could have been a car door.

122
00:05:20,862 --> 00:05:21,904
It's possible.

123
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:24,073
[suave music playing]

124
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:25,450
You're a smart one, Atoy.

125
00:05:26,617 --> 00:05:28,995
At this point,
we need to identify that vehicle.

126
00:05:30,246 --> 00:05:31,164
Right?

127
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:33,207
[suave music playing]

128
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:34,917
FATHER'S LANE
FOOD HUB IN BACLARAN

129
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:36,961
[suave opening theme music]

130
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:20,671
[somber music]

131
00:06:36,187 --> 00:06:37,772
You shouldn't have talked to him.

132
00:06:39,857 --> 00:06:42,485
I just want him to feel

133
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:47,240
and gave him assurance
that whatever you did,

134
00:06:47,323 --> 00:06:48,866
you still love him.

135
00:06:50,535 --> 00:06:52,787
[sniffs] All you did was waste your time.

136
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:54,330
[somber music playing]

137
00:06:54,413 --> 00:06:55,706
Atoy has always been stubborn…

138
00:06:57,166 --> 00:06:59,127
[scoffs] Ever since.

139
00:07:01,045 --> 00:07:03,256
He will not turn his shoulder on me,
specially now.

140
00:07:05,466 --> 00:07:07,343
Come on. Don't think like that.

141
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:11,514
His anger comes from a place of love,

142
00:07:11,597 --> 00:07:14,684
and one day he’ll learn
to see that love in himself.

143
00:07:14,767 --> 00:07:16,185
That’s what I’ll keep praying for.

144
00:07:17,311 --> 00:07:20,440
There are prayers to God
that go unanswered.

145
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:21,816
I know.

146
00:07:21,899 --> 00:07:27,113
And yet, despite everything,
He still took his mother from us.

147
00:07:27,196 --> 00:07:29,532
[somber music continues]

148
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:50,428
Hi, sir! Welcome to Boorjer,
home of the best burgers in town.

149
00:07:50,511 --> 00:07:51,429
What is your order, sir?

150
00:07:51,512 --> 00:07:54,432
Miss, is the route that everyone takes
to get to the church?

151
00:07:54,515 --> 00:07:57,185
Yes, sir, since the other end is blocked.

152
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:59,562
[brazen music playing]

153
00:07:59,645 --> 00:08:01,397
[server] Ah… Oh, sir, sir. Sir!

154
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:02,732
You're not allowed to sleep there, sir.

155
00:08:02,815 --> 00:08:05,276
[Atoy] Don't worry. He's with me.

156
00:08:06,777 --> 00:08:10,490
[brazen music continues]

157
00:08:18,247 --> 00:08:21,667
Miss, your CCTV records everyone
who walks by, right?

158
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:24,170
Could I…

159
00:08:24,253 --> 00:08:27,215
Could I take a look at the footage
from the other night?

160
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:28,633
I'm just trying to find something.

161
00:08:28,716 --> 00:08:29,842
Pardon?

162
00:08:30,676 --> 00:08:32,386
But I have no clue how to operate it, sir.

163
00:08:32,970 --> 00:08:34,138
Ah.

164
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:36,682
Miss!

165
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:39,852
I will buy every burger you have.

166
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:42,772
That includes all the meat,
the ketchup, everything.

167
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:43,773
What?

168
00:08:45,691 --> 00:08:47,276
[Atoy] Yes, all you need
to give me now is the receipt.

169
00:08:47,985 --> 00:08:48,986
Sure.

170
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:50,780
Okay.

171
00:08:52,281 --> 00:08:54,116
Atoy, I'm heading back to the church.

172
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,576
Any news?

173
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:58,704
- Yes, I managed to speak to Sir Nestor.
- [sinister music]

174
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:01,374
Even if that man isn’t quite himself,

175
00:09:01,457 --> 00:09:04,502
I still managed to get a lead
from him about Saint Anthony.

176
00:09:04,585 --> 00:09:07,421
I’m tracking a plate number.

177
00:09:08,005 --> 00:09:10,049
It’s registered in…

178
00:09:10,132 --> 00:09:13,135
DPR Trucking Services.

179
00:09:14,428 --> 00:09:15,805
DPR Trucking?

180
00:09:16,597 --> 00:09:18,474
That place is quite far from here.

181
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:19,600
But I think…

182
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:23,271
I think I’ve passed
by that compound before.

183
00:09:29,151 --> 00:09:29,986
Wow.

184
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:31,612
I see…

185
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:33,656
you make quite the effort
to go everywhere.

186
00:09:34,657 --> 00:09:35,950
Ah, yes.

187
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:38,119
It's because I have a lot of clients.

188
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:40,746
Some of them, I visit personally.

189
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:44,584
So the woman I saw you
talking to outside the apartelle…

190
00:09:45,459 --> 00:09:46,460
Is she one of your clients too?

191
00:09:46,544 --> 00:09:48,296
[music intensifies]

192
00:09:49,005 --> 00:09:51,424
- An apartelle, of all places?
- Atoy…

193
00:09:51,507 --> 00:09:53,968
How did it feel playing around
with your measuring tape?

194
00:09:55,636 --> 00:09:58,973
Or how many sessions did it take
to get the fit just right?

195
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:02,059
Three? Four? Like that?

196
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:04,770
Tell me. Was it tight or loose?

197
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:07,273
Come on, speak up! Tell me the truth!

198
00:10:07,356 --> 00:10:08,524
- [thuds]
- Enough!

199
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:09,942
You're crossing the line!

200
00:10:12,653 --> 00:10:14,155
You're one to talk!

201
00:10:14,238 --> 00:10:15,740
[tense music playing]

202
00:10:16,324 --> 00:10:18,159
After what you did with that woman,

203
00:10:18,242 --> 00:10:19,869
you're really going to come home,

204
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:22,663
kiss and hug my mother,

205
00:10:22,747 --> 00:10:24,332
and pretend like nothing ever happened?

206
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,334
You're the shameless one here.

207
00:10:27,835 --> 00:10:29,629
I used to look up to you.

208
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:32,548
I believed you were a decent man.

209
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:34,717
But you're not.

210
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:36,636
You have no idea how much anger
you've caused me.

211
00:10:37,219 --> 00:10:40,306
But no matter how hard I try,
I can't stop thinking about you.

212
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:43,851
I was actually about to tell her.

213
00:10:43,934 --> 00:10:45,603
I was ready to tell Mom.

214
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:47,188
I was ready to expose everything.

215
00:10:47,271 --> 00:10:48,481
But for what?

216
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:50,316
To hurt her even more?

217
00:10:50,399 --> 00:10:54,153
To watch her heart shatter because of you?

218
00:10:54,236 --> 00:10:57,239
- [Cita] Stop it, Delfin! That's enough!
- I loved your mother!

219
00:10:57,323 --> 00:10:59,450
- [Cita] Enough already!
- I loved my wife.

220
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:01,160
She was the only woman I ever truly loved.

221
00:11:01,243 --> 00:11:02,119
No one else!

222
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,037
[Cita] Enough!

223
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:06,791
That's enough!

224
00:11:06,874 --> 00:11:09,251
- I know I made a mistake.
- [Cita crying]

225
00:11:10,711 --> 00:11:12,713
But I love my wife so much!

226
00:11:12,797 --> 00:11:15,174
It's ironic that you can
admit your mistakes.

227
00:11:17,426 --> 00:11:21,180
But when you cheated on her,
it's your choice.

228
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:24,183
[pensive music playing]

229
00:11:24,266 --> 00:11:25,351
That’s enough. [crying]

230
00:11:31,315 --> 00:11:33,734
I’m going to find the statue now.

231
00:11:34,568 --> 00:11:36,153
I’ll return it to the church

232
00:11:36,737 --> 00:11:38,656
because it belongs to my mother.

233
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:41,575
My mother…

234
00:11:44,829 --> 00:11:46,163
who loved you…

235
00:11:48,916 --> 00:11:50,000
But you betrayed her anyway.

236
00:11:53,295 --> 00:11:55,339
After that, we’re done.

237
00:11:55,423 --> 00:11:57,716
[pensive music continues]

238
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:26,579
[pensive music continues]

239
00:12:31,292 --> 00:12:34,628
[sniffling and sobbing]

240
00:12:39,216 --> 00:12:43,471
- [pensive music continues]
- [sniffling]

241
00:13:32,019 --> 00:13:34,563
- [pensive music concludes]
- [hooter honks]

242
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:37,525
Hi, sir! Your order is finally here.

243
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,777
Thank you so much, sir!

244
00:13:40,778 --> 00:13:41,904
Miss, do you know…

245
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:44,198
where the drunk man from earlier went?

246
00:13:44,281 --> 00:13:46,116
He's already left, sir.

247
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,493
He said he's going to keep drinking.

248
00:13:48,285 --> 00:13:49,411
[scoffs]

249
00:13:50,788 --> 00:13:51,622
‪[tick]

250
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:55,834
Miss.

251
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:58,254
I have just two more favors to ask of you.

252
00:13:59,004 --> 00:14:00,464
[brazen music playing]

253
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:01,674
What-- What are they, sir?

254
00:14:01,757 --> 00:14:03,801
Can you lend me your delivery motorbike?

255
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:08,472
Also, do you happen
to have an extra uniform?

256
00:14:13,811 --> 00:14:15,563
[hooter honks]

257
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:20,526
[brazen music continues]

258
00:14:21,402 --> 00:14:22,236
What's that?

259
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:25,239
- Sir! Good evening, sir!
- Oh.

260
00:14:25,322 --> 00:14:27,491
Delivery, sir, from Mr. Boorjer,

261
00:14:27,575 --> 00:14:29,451
home of the best burgers in town.

262
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:32,121
We never placed an order.

263
00:14:32,204 --> 00:14:33,706
But sir…

264
00:14:34,748 --> 00:14:41,463
Isn’t this the DPR Trucking Compound
at 34 Balayong Street?

265
00:14:41,547 --> 00:14:43,424
Sir, I believe this is your order.

266
00:14:44,383 --> 00:14:46,552
Also, this is our best-seller.

267
00:14:46,635 --> 00:14:48,345
And I've brought three full bags of it.

268
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:51,390
Well, sir, would you like to try one?

269
00:14:51,473 --> 00:14:53,851
[chuckles] All right. Come on!

270
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,477
[sighs] Let me see…

271
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:57,730
All right then. See…

272
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:00,274
Oh.

273
00:15:00,357 --> 00:15:02,902
This is your order.
The address matches, right?

274
00:15:02,985 --> 00:15:05,571
Ah, maybe Merly ordered this.

275
00:15:05,654 --> 00:15:07,281
She's probably paying for it.

276
00:15:07,364 --> 00:15:08,782
Merly?

277
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:10,993
Right! That's the name on the order slip.

278
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:13,287
I knew it! [chuckles]

279
00:15:13,370 --> 00:15:14,455
Well…

280
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:16,206
Would you like me to give this to her?

281
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:17,666
I'll bring it in, sir.

282
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:20,544
All right, come in.

283
00:15:20,628 --> 00:15:22,129
Awesome! You can put that right there.

284
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:27,635
- Um, Miss… Merly? Merly?
- Hm-mm.

285
00:15:27,718 --> 00:15:32,723
I have a delivery from Mr. Boorjer,
home of the best burgers in town.

286
00:15:32,806 --> 00:15:35,559
I didn't order this many burgers.

287
00:15:35,643 --> 00:15:37,061
Hmm… That's odd.

288
00:15:37,686 --> 00:15:40,814
Miss, could this be from a…

289
00:15:41,982 --> 00:15:45,277
secret admirer? Oh, wow! [chuckling]

290
00:15:45,361 --> 00:15:46,820
With a beauty like yours,

291
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:50,115
I bet you have plenty of admirers.

292
00:15:50,199 --> 00:15:52,159
Too bad they'll all have to wait.

293
00:15:52,242 --> 00:15:53,369
Are you for real?

294
00:15:54,203 --> 00:15:57,206
Uh… Uh…

295
00:15:58,415 --> 00:16:00,918
Miss, may I…

296
00:16:01,710 --> 00:16:03,837
- use the restroom?
- What for?

297
00:16:03,921 --> 00:16:05,422
[funky music playing]

298
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:08,926
Because I need a moment to catch
my breath. [groans] Smooth, huh?

299
00:16:09,009 --> 00:16:09,885
[both laugh]

300
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:10,928
- Right this way.
- [chuckling]

301
00:16:11,595 --> 00:16:13,764
[funky music continues]

302
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:24,817
[suave music playing]

303
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:41,834
[rattles]

304
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:45,587
[suave music continues]

305
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:10,821
[Red grunting]

306
00:17:13,782 --> 00:17:15,909
Sir Mongki, I have something
for you and Sir Red.

307
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:17,202
[Mongki] Hmm?

308
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:20,998
[Red whooshing, grunting]

309
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:29,089
[curious music playing]

310
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:31,508
[in English] What the hell is that smell?

311
00:17:32,342 --> 00:17:33,969
Cheap ketchup!

312
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:39,141
Sir, I think this is from…
Mr. Boorjer, the burger joint.

313
00:17:41,143 --> 00:17:42,394
Tastes fine to me.

314
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:44,104
Sir, it was delivered to me earlier.

315
00:17:44,188 --> 00:17:45,272
Twenty-nine pieces.

316
00:17:45,355 --> 00:17:47,816
I'll also send them out
to the other drivers and staff later.

317
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:48,859
Who's it from?

318
00:17:48,942 --> 00:17:50,319
A secret admirer of mine, sir.

319
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:53,614
- Who exactly?
- Well, it's a secret.

320
00:17:55,741 --> 00:17:57,159
[in English] Stupid.

321
00:17:58,535 --> 00:18:01,413
You’re not attractive enough
to have a secret admirer.

322
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:03,791
Spit that out!

323
00:18:04,541 --> 00:18:08,670
You shouldn’t be accepting
deliveries from strangers.

324
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:10,672
Didn’t they teach you that
in kindergarten?

325
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:13,675
Especially now,
with the kind of work we do!

326
00:18:15,385 --> 00:18:16,261
Where's the delivery guy?

327
00:18:16,345 --> 00:18:18,847
He went to the restroom. I'm sorry.

328
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:22,935
Mongki, take Hansel with you.

329
00:18:23,018 --> 00:18:25,687
[curious music continues]

330
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:31,568
[inquisitive music playing]

331
00:18:53,549 --> 00:18:55,551
It’s about eight centimeters.

332
00:18:55,634 --> 00:18:57,803
Wider than an ordinary tire.

333
00:19:00,180 --> 00:19:01,390
A container truck.

334
00:19:02,474 --> 00:19:05,185
[inquisitive music continues]

335
00:19:16,738 --> 00:19:18,574
Ivory fragments.

336
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:23,579
You know, the patron’s face and hands
are made from legally acquired ivory.

337
00:19:24,204 --> 00:19:25,330
[in English] Container truck…

338
00:19:25,414 --> 00:19:27,457
[in English] Ivory fragments…

339
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:29,293
Here.

340
00:19:29,376 --> 00:19:31,420
This is where Saint Anthony was brought.

341
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:33,255
He just left.

342
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:35,007
I need to catch up--

343
00:19:35,090 --> 00:19:36,884
[uneasy music playing]

344
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:38,302
Who are you? Are you a cop?

345
00:19:38,385 --> 00:19:41,263
Um, no, sir, I'm not.

346
00:19:41,346 --> 00:19:42,848
[brazen music playing]

347
00:19:42,931 --> 00:19:43,765
Sir, sir, please…

348
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:47,769
Please, sir. Sir, please, don't.

349
00:19:48,478 --> 00:19:49,313
What are you doing here?

350
00:19:49,396 --> 00:19:50,939
The restroom is way over there.

351
00:19:51,481 --> 00:19:53,609
Who are you, really?! Are you a cop?!

352
00:19:55,694 --> 00:19:56,862
Delfin…

353
00:19:57,446 --> 00:20:00,949
I just wanted to apologize to you again.

354
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:05,245
I know I’m the reason things went wrong
between you and Atoy.

355
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:10,417
- What's done is done, Cita.
- [melancholic music]

356
00:20:12,753 --> 00:20:14,004
I don't think that is the reason

357
00:20:14,087 --> 00:20:16,506
why my son spare me.

358
00:20:16,590 --> 00:20:19,259
I'm sorry you had to see
how upset he was earlier.

359
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:21,011
Don't apologize.

360
00:20:21,887 --> 00:20:24,973
I think I needed to see it and feel it,

361
00:20:25,057 --> 00:20:26,808
for me to know

362
00:20:28,018 --> 00:20:30,312
that I hurt Atoy,

363
00:20:30,395 --> 00:20:32,272
that I broke your family.

364
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:37,277
I don't know if…

365
00:20:38,111 --> 00:20:41,573
if I should feel relief or suffer knowing…

366
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:45,827
that he doesn't even know
I'm the woman who was with you.

367
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:48,830
Things between you and Atoy
should remain the same.

368
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:52,542
For him, that may be
the case, but not for me.

369
00:20:53,543 --> 00:20:55,754
His anger sits heavy in my heart.

370
00:20:55,837 --> 00:20:58,215
I’m the reason why he’s so hurt.

371
00:20:59,841 --> 00:21:02,761
Atoy trusted me.

372
00:21:02,844 --> 00:21:04,805
He looked up to me like a mother.

373
00:21:04,888 --> 00:21:08,058
How can I live with myself
knowing that, even now,

374
00:21:08,141 --> 00:21:11,645
I’ve been deceiving him
by keeping the truth from him?

375
00:21:11,728 --> 00:21:12,562
‪[Delfin sobs]

376
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:17,192
So what do you want to happen now?

377
00:21:17,859 --> 00:21:21,405
He needs to know that I'm
the woman who was with you.

378
00:21:22,322 --> 00:21:23,156
‪[sobs]

379
00:21:23,865 --> 00:21:24,700
‪[scoffs]

380
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:27,327
No, Cita, no.

381
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:29,955
- No.
- [Cita crying]

382
00:21:30,038 --> 00:21:32,958
It will only make things harder for Atoy.

383
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:35,669
What he truly needs is a family!

384
00:21:35,752 --> 00:21:37,296
He needs you!

385
00:21:39,256 --> 00:21:44,636
I can't abandon him in this world
filled with so much anger.

386
00:21:50,475 --> 00:21:52,060
What do you mean?

387
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:54,521
[pensive music playing]

388
00:21:54,604 --> 00:21:55,439
Well…

389
00:21:58,275 --> 00:22:00,402
I'm suffering from a condition.

390
00:22:00,485 --> 00:22:02,154
I don't have much time left.

391
00:22:02,821 --> 00:22:07,743
[pensive music continues]

392
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:12,289
Speak up!

393
00:22:12,372 --> 00:22:13,623
No, sir! I'm not a cop!

394
00:22:13,707 --> 00:22:16,084
- [inquisitive music playing]
- Uh…

395
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:17,836
Sir, my name is Ernesto Manalo.

396
00:22:17,919 --> 00:22:19,212
Sir, I have two children.

397
00:22:19,296 --> 00:22:22,257
And my mother is on dialysis as well.

398
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:24,134
I'm also separated from my wife.

399
00:22:24,217 --> 00:22:25,093
Please, sir, sir.

400
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:26,845
I'm just an ordinary delivery rider.

401
00:22:26,928 --> 00:22:29,639
Please don't… I'm begging you…
I'm not a cop. I'm not a cop, sir.

402
00:22:29,723 --> 00:22:31,683
I'm begging you… I was just…
I was just tying my shoelaces

403
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:33,560
when you caught me here, sir.

404
00:22:33,643 --> 00:22:36,396
Sir, I'm begging you. Don't do it, please.

405
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,564
Turn around! Faster!

406
00:22:37,647 --> 00:22:38,648
Sir!

407
00:22:38,732 --> 00:22:39,566
‪[whimpering]

408
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:42,444
Sir…

409
00:22:44,362 --> 00:22:45,781
- [whimpering]
- [chuckling]

410
00:22:45,864 --> 00:22:48,408
Sir, I'm nothing more
than a delivery guy from Mr. Boorjer.

411
00:22:48,492 --> 00:22:49,743
Mr. Boor--

412
00:22:49,826 --> 00:22:51,244
I'm just from Mr. Boorjer, sir.

413
00:22:51,328 --> 00:22:53,747
[speaking indistinctly]

414
00:22:53,830 --> 00:22:55,624
I could have shot you
right then and there.

415
00:22:56,249 --> 00:22:57,793
But you already told me
your whole sob story.

416
00:22:59,377 --> 00:23:00,962
Get up! Up!

417
00:23:07,427 --> 00:23:09,137
[inquisitive music playing]

418
00:23:09,221 --> 00:23:10,430
I highly doubt he's a cop.

419
00:23:11,223 --> 00:23:12,474
Check further.

420
00:23:13,266 --> 00:23:14,226
Let me see your hands.

421
00:23:16,603 --> 00:23:20,273
Is that mustache
a part of your uniform, huh?

422
00:23:20,357 --> 00:23:21,775
- Fix it.
- Yes, sir.

423
00:23:21,858 --> 00:23:25,612
Mr. Boorjer, delivery for you, sir.

424
00:23:25,695 --> 00:23:29,449
Go back to wherever
you came from, Ernesto Manalo.

425
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:31,118
And don't you ever come back!

426
00:23:35,413 --> 00:23:40,293
[stirring music playing]

427
00:23:55,016 --> 00:23:56,560
[dramatic musical flourishing]

428
00:23:57,477 --> 00:23:59,521
[engine whirring]

429
00:23:59,604 --> 00:24:02,315
[upbeat curious music playing]

430
00:24:03,650 --> 00:24:07,571
It's finally coming.
The VPR's been inside for a while now.

431
00:24:22,544 --> 00:24:25,755
[upbeat curious music continues]

432
00:24:51,156 --> 00:24:54,534
[ship horn blares]

433
00:24:55,744 --> 00:25:00,957
[inquisitive music playing]

434
00:25:09,257 --> 00:25:13,428
Mongki said that Merly
bought burgers for everyone,

435
00:25:13,511 --> 00:25:15,347
but Sir Red just threw them away.

436
00:25:15,430 --> 00:25:16,264
What a waste.

437
00:25:16,348 --> 00:25:18,016
[worker 2] Wish they had
given it to us instead.

438
00:25:18,099 --> 00:25:19,351
[worker 1] Let's eat first.

439
00:25:19,434 --> 00:25:21,937
We still have 30 minutes before
everything gets moved onto the barge.

440
00:25:22,020 --> 00:25:23,730
Where are your people?

441
00:25:23,813 --> 00:25:25,607
- They're on their way here. Let's go.
- [worker 1] Okay.

442
00:25:31,905 --> 00:25:35,492
[inquisitive music continues]

443
00:25:46,962 --> 00:25:48,213
[creaks]

444
00:25:55,428 --> 00:25:59,015
[inquisitive music continues]

445
00:26:13,446 --> 00:26:17,158
[inquisitive music continues]

446
00:26:20,287 --> 00:26:21,913
- Ivory smuggling.
- [tense music playing]

447
00:26:23,873 --> 00:26:25,500
[phone keys beeping]

448
00:26:25,583 --> 00:26:27,335
[line ringing]

449
00:26:27,961 --> 00:26:30,380
Mate, I need you to send
a cop over to the port.

450
00:26:31,548 --> 00:26:33,550
[sighs] DPR.

451
00:26:33,633 --> 00:26:34,759
DPR Shipping.

452
00:26:34,843 --> 00:26:38,388
That's the name of the container
we need to stop, okay?

453
00:26:38,471 --> 00:26:43,518
- [stirring music playing]
- [heavy breathing]

454
00:26:47,897 --> 00:26:49,065
Bingo.

455
00:26:51,151 --> 00:26:57,198
[inquisitive music playing]

456
00:27:03,747 --> 00:27:07,042
[chuckles softly]

457
00:27:08,793 --> 00:27:10,211
Hello.

458
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:11,880
Finally, we meet.

459
00:27:11,963 --> 00:27:13,631
Don't worry.

460
00:27:14,215 --> 00:27:17,427
I'll get you home if you help me out.

461
00:27:17,510 --> 00:27:19,679
I'm counting on you, okay?

462
00:27:19,763 --> 00:27:20,889
Let's go.

463
00:27:21,806 --> 00:27:23,683
Let's go, let's go, let's go…

464
00:27:23,767 --> 00:27:25,310
Wait a sec.

465
00:27:25,393 --> 00:27:26,895
I forgot to lock the container.

466
00:27:27,645 --> 00:27:28,480
‪[tense music]

467
00:27:29,606 --> 00:27:30,940
Why is this open?

468
00:27:31,691 --> 00:27:35,070
[brazen music playing]

469
00:27:42,369 --> 00:27:47,749
[brazen music continues]

470
00:27:56,841 --> 00:27:58,968
[Atoy] Good evening to you.

471
00:28:00,053 --> 00:28:01,679
- [thuds]
- [grunting]

472
00:28:01,763 --> 00:28:03,765
[tense energetic music playing]

473
00:28:03,848 --> 00:28:05,809
- [thuds]
- [grunting]

474
00:28:09,229 --> 00:28:11,106
[thudding]

475
00:28:12,148 --> 00:28:13,400
[thuds]

476
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:16,861
[gun firing]

477
00:28:16,945 --> 00:28:18,655
Sir, drop the gun!

478
00:28:18,738 --> 00:28:20,365
There are plenty of saints watching.

479
00:28:20,448 --> 00:28:21,825
Do you really want to end up in hell?

480
00:28:26,579 --> 00:28:29,249
[grunting]

481
00:28:30,583 --> 00:28:31,668
[thuds]

482
00:28:31,751 --> 00:28:33,253
[grunting]

483
00:28:34,003 --> 00:28:35,380
- [crane creaks]
- [grunts]

484
00:28:36,673 --> 00:28:37,590
[tense music playing]

485
00:28:42,345 --> 00:28:44,431
[crane creaks]

486
00:28:46,224 --> 00:28:47,559
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

487
00:28:48,309 --> 00:28:49,352
[thudding]

488
00:28:52,147 --> 00:28:53,857
Hey, hey, hey!

489
00:28:59,487 --> 00:29:02,949
Security, security. Someone's hanging
from the DPR container.

490
00:29:05,034 --> 00:29:08,830
[brazen music playing]

491
00:29:08,913 --> 00:29:14,169
[gun firing]

492
00:29:19,007 --> 00:29:23,219
[electronic blipping]

493
00:29:26,055 --> 00:29:27,640
[intense music playing]

494
00:29:27,724 --> 00:29:30,059
[in English] You told me
everything is going well.

495
00:29:30,143 --> 00:29:31,352
I will look for him.

496
00:29:31,436 --> 00:29:32,979
UP NEXT

497
00:29:33,062 --> 00:29:34,606
[in English] No one crosses a Regalia.

498
00:29:34,689 --> 00:29:37,859
I heard the patron
has returned last night.

499
00:29:37,942 --> 00:29:40,278
[woman] What are we waiting for?!
Come on, let's go!

500
00:29:40,361 --> 00:29:43,406
- Wow, the patron really is back.
- [Paldo] But how?

501
00:29:43,490 --> 00:29:45,575
- Who could have returned it?
- Him.

502
00:29:45,658 --> 00:29:48,369
Sir, we need to make that monster pay.

503
00:29:48,453 --> 00:29:49,370
Bang!

504
00:29:50,455 --> 00:29:51,998
There he is.

505
00:29:55,543 --> 00:29:57,378
[tires screeching]

506
00:29:58,671 --> 00:30:01,549
Subtitle translation by:
Inocencio Cañete Raman Jr.
